This paper discusses a novel computational architecture for general image feature mining, which is a problem related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of boosting algorithms, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of primitive filters and compositional features, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on public datasets, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
